name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellant, v. William R. GRIBBLE, Appellant

parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellant, v. William R. GRIBBLE, Appellant.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM
AND NOW, this 4th day of December, 1998, the Emergency Motion for Extension of Stay of Execution is dismissed without prejudice to William R. Gribble to seek a stay of execution upon the issuance of a warrant of execution.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM

casebody.head_matter:
721 A.2d 54
COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellant, v. William R. GRIBBLE, Appellant.
Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
Dec. 4, 1998.
